d7108cef7835"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Pentagonal numbers are generated by the formula, Pn=n(3n\[Minus]1)/2. The \
first ten pentagonal numbers are:\n\n1, 5, 12, 22, 35, 51, 70, 92, 117, 145, \
...\n\nIt can be seen that P4 + P7 = 22 + 70 = 92 = P8. However, their \
difference, 70 \[Minus] 22 = 48, is not pentagonal.\n\nFind the pair of \
pentagonal numbers, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["P", "j"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3160b6d8-df6e-4d56-91fd-055083339053"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["P", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9465902a-3a15-4e54-9c60-ded6d853d777"],
 ", for which their sum and difference are pentagonal and D = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"|", 
    SubscriptBox["P", "k"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2a939ae0-2f94-41d2-bb4b-bfb601f61d1b"],
 " \[Minus] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["P", "j"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3fc80e0b-eaea-4227-9336-0356d70f0854"],
 "| is minimized; what is the value of D?"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.650820894713208*^9, 3.6508208961976004`*^9}, {
